    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>East India Chambers, Leadenhall St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName>, <date>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> July
                    1862</date></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <add>חברת מרביצי תורה</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">JEWISH ASSOCIATION FOR THE DIFFUSION</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">OF RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE.</p>
            <p>Rev Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Will you be so kind as to inform<lb/> me at what price per hundred
                you<lb/> would be willing to supply your<lb/> translation of the Bible to the
                above<lb/> association.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I trust you will name the<lb/> lowest possible cost, as the
                Association<lb/> require the Bibles for gratuitous distribution<lb/> among the
                poor.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If it be not too much<lb/> trouble, I should feel obliged by
                your<lb/> furnishing two separate estimates,<lb/> one for the Bible bound, complete,
                as<lb/> supplied by your agent in <placeName>London</placeName>,k<lb/> and the other
                for the Bible in reams,<lb/> un-bound.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Awaiting your reply,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I have the honor to be, Rev Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Your obedt Servt.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">N. S. Joseph</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Hon Secry</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
